      "message": "Just use an event promise[1] in your beforeEach().\n\n  let ignoresPageSk;\n\n  beforeEach(() \u003d\u003e {\n    const endTaskEvent \u003d eventPromise(\u0027end-task\u0027);\n    ignoresPageSk \u003d newIgnoresPageSk(); // Instantiate your component under test.\n    await endTaskEvent;\n  });\n\nThen write your tests directly:\n\n  it(\u0027should do something\u0027, () \u003d\u003e {\n    expect(ignoresPageSk.foo()).to.equal(\u0027bar\u0027);\n  });\n\nBenefits: More concise, no need to nest your tests inside a callback.\n\nhttps://cs.corp.google.com/skia/buildbot/golden/modules/test_util.js?l\u003d59",
